Separate small Makefile/tools (certs, server info)
Configuration knobs (Makefile)
You set NAME (FQDN; short name becomes libvirt domain name), DISTRO, ROLE, ENV, RAM/VCPUs, disk sizes (ROOTSIZE, SWAPSIZE, DATASIZE, …), NET, and paths like ETCDIR, VARDIR, DATADIR. Defaults point at /var/lib/kvmbld-style layout and qemu:///system.

Caveats
setup in the repo root is not a shell “setup script”; it reads like captured Ansible JSON output (large file).
Templates contain secrets (password hashes, SSH public keys, proxy URLs) — treat the repo as sensitive if it matches production.
noblemin line in distro is missing a trailing ;filename field unlike others; that could break cut -f4 for that row depending on use.
In one sentence: autobuild is your personal “Ubuntu cloud image → qcow2 + cloud-init by role → virt-install + Ansible hook” factory for KVM lab/production nodes.
